records.addlTxt:
State moves to amend the charge from felony bail jumping to misdemeanor bail jumping, contrary to Section 946.49(1)(b) of the Wisconsin Statutes.   Motion granted.  No contest plea to the amended charge.  Convicted.   Sentence is withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for one (1) year.   Conditions of probation are: 
1) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process only if one has not already been done;
2) Maintain full-time employment/schooling combination;
3) Maintain absolute sobriety;
4) Pay costs of action;
5) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined;
6) Reimburse Manitowoc County for attorney fees.
Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights. 
Minutes.
